1
00:00:07,774 --> 00:00:08,808
Ayaka.

2
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:11,378
Here's your lunch.

3
00:00:11,878 --> 00:00:14,280
I put in your favorite Hamburg steak
to cheer you up!

4
00:00:14,914 --> 00:00:15,749
Thanks.

5
00:00:18,485 --> 00:00:20,320
- Be careful.
- Okay.

6
00:00:20,887 --> 00:00:21,821
Bye.

7
00:00:31,798 --> 00:00:32,799
You've got this!

8
00:00:39,272 --> 00:00:42,442
MUSASHINO KITA MIDDLE SCHOOL

9
00:00:47,914 --> 00:00:50,049
YUKANAI

10
00:00:50,050 --> 00:00:52,951
YUKANAI
NOW ACCEPTING NEW STUDENTS!

11
00:00:52,952 --> 00:00:54,254
Ready, smash!

12
00:00:59,292 --> 00:01:00,726
Oh, no.

13
00:01:00,727 --> 00:01:02,561
I'm losing.

14
00:01:02,562 --> 00:01:04,731
Yuuki. What are you making?

15
00:01:05,498 --> 00:01:07,967
An alien. An evil one.

16
00:01:08,868 --> 00:01:11,071
Oh, that's scary. Should we take him down?

17
00:01:12,005 --> 00:01:13,106
How should we do it?

18
00:01:15,208 --> 00:01:16,409
Wanna make something?

19
00:01:17,143 --> 00:01:18,344
No, it's okay.

20
00:01:20,046 --> 00:01:21,147
Okay.

21
00:01:39,499 --> 00:01:40,699
Forget it!

22
00:01:40,700 --> 00:01:42,367
- I'm sick of this!
- Whoa!

23
00:01:42,368 --> 00:01:44,137
That's right! Take 'em down!

24
00:01:47,073 --> 00:01:48,041
Yuuki!

25
00:01:49,175 --> 00:01:50,543
The demon's here.

26
00:01:51,177 --> 00:01:52,611
Come at me!

27
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:53,780
Shut up!

28
00:01:54,948 --> 00:01:56,549
Oh… um…

29
00:01:57,750 --> 00:01:58,650
I'm sorry.

30
00:01:58,651 --> 00:02:00,486
I'm here for the interview.

31
00:02:00,487 --> 00:02:01,854
- Great timing.
- Um…

32
00:02:01,855 --> 00:02:02,754
Put this on.

33
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:03,922
‎What?

34
00:02:03,923 --> 00:02:06,925
Yuuki! The blue demon is here too.

35
00:02:06,926 --> 00:02:07,893
What?

36
00:02:07,894 --> 00:02:09,261
Go away!

37
00:02:09,262 --> 00:02:10,662
- Go get 'em!
- Wait a minute!

38
00:02:10,663 --> 00:02:11,563
Throw harder!

39
00:02:11,564 --> 00:02:12,665
What?

40
00:02:13,366 --> 00:02:14,833
- Hold on! It hurts.
- Come get me!

41
00:02:14,834 --> 00:02:15,668
Ouch!

42
00:02:24,878 --> 00:02:28,881
350,000 CHILDREN EXPERIENCE SCHOOL REFUSAL

43
00:02:28,882 --> 00:02:31,116
WHAT'S AN ALTERNATIVE SCHOOL?
A PLACE TO RECLAIM AND NURTURE YOURSELF

44
00:02:31,117 --> 00:02:33,419
"THIRD SAFE HAVEN"
ASIDE FROM SCHOOL OR HOME

45
00:02:34,254 --> 00:02:37,624
Those guys really don't hold back.
They're always like that.

46
00:02:38,958 --> 00:02:41,160
Anyway, you're here
for the interview, right?

47
00:02:41,161 --> 00:02:42,528
Yes.

48
00:02:42,529 --> 00:02:44,731
- Please sit.
- Thank you.

49
00:02:45,598 --> 00:02:47,167
Thank you.

50
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:52,538
Okay.

51
00:02:52,539 --> 00:02:55,107
I'm here on a referral
from Professor Mikumo.

52
00:02:55,108 --> 00:02:58,311
I'm scheduled to have an interview
with the manager.

53
00:03:01,214 --> 00:03:02,782
Um… Where's the manager?

54
00:03:03,283 --> 00:03:04,484
That's me.

55
00:03:05,618 --> 00:03:07,352
Oh, I apologize.

56
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:08,921
I'm Tatsuki Ukita, the manager.

57
00:03:08,922 --> 00:03:11,924
I'm Shizuku Aomine.

58
00:03:11,925 --> 00:03:12,925
Ao…

59
00:03:12,926 --> 00:03:13,960
Aom…

60
00:03:14,494 --> 00:03:16,329
- Aomine…
- Shizuku Aomine.

61
00:03:17,263 --> 00:03:19,432
Please just call me Shizuku.

62
00:03:21,601 --> 00:03:23,502
- Ms. Shizuku.
- Yes.

63
00:03:23,503 --> 00:03:24,971
You were…

64
00:03:25,805 --> 00:03:28,173
You were a teacher
at Musashino Daihachi Middle School?

65
00:03:28,174 --> 00:03:29,309
Yes.

66
00:03:29,909 --> 00:03:32,011
I worked as a teacher
for about five years,

67
00:03:32,512 --> 00:03:34,180
but I left due to personal reasons.

68
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:36,616
Why this alternative school?

69
00:03:37,183 --> 00:03:40,820
I really want to continue working
with children.

70
00:03:43,489 --> 00:03:44,523
You play video games?

71
00:03:44,524 --> 00:03:46,059
- What?
- Video games.

72
00:03:46,893 --> 00:03:48,861
I've never played them before.

73
00:03:49,429 --> 00:03:51,864
Then what about shogi,
card games, or board games?

74
00:03:53,066 --> 00:03:53,933
Sorry, no.

75
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:55,602
I see.

76
00:03:57,370 --> 00:03:58,737
Any other special skills?

77
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,505
I can tutor.

78
00:04:00,506 --> 00:04:02,976
For Japanese and English,
I can teach from basics to advanced.

79
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:05,211
That's not what I meant.

80
00:04:07,447 --> 00:04:09,182
Do you own a hoodie?

81
00:04:09,716 --> 00:04:11,017
- Hoodie?
- Yeah.

82
00:04:12,118 --> 00:04:13,318
Yes, I believe so.

83
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:14,354
Okay.

84
00:04:15,255 --> 00:04:18,057
But you can't play games, huh.

85
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:20,593
Tatsuki.

86
00:04:21,561 --> 00:04:22,861
They want to go outside.

87
00:04:22,862 --> 00:04:24,329
I want to play color tag.

88
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:25,964
Good idea.

89
00:04:25,965 --> 00:04:27,199
Let's see…

90
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:28,968
What should I do?

91
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:33,772
I'll contact you
with the results at a later date.

92
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:34,607
Thank you.

93
00:04:36,342 --> 00:04:37,510
Um…

94
00:04:38,311 --> 00:04:39,412
I…

95
00:04:41,281 --> 00:04:43,883
didn't go to school for six years
starting in middle school.

96
00:04:44,384 --> 00:04:47,219
So I think I understand
the feelings of kids

97
00:04:47,220 --> 00:04:48,821
experiencing school refusal.

98
00:04:49,389 --> 00:04:51,324
That's my special skill!

99
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:11,878
You're hired.

100
00:05:14,881 --> 00:05:16,215
You're hired.

101
00:05:17,183 --> 00:05:18,918
You're hired.

102
00:05:21,821 --> 00:05:24,323
I'm Soya Kaido, a volunteer staff member.

103
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:25,858
Everyone calls me Soya.

104
00:05:26,426 --> 00:05:27,426
Mr. Soya.

105
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:29,394
I'm Shizuku Aomine.

106
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:31,430
- Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

107
00:05:31,431 --> 00:05:33,732
Everyone here calls each other
by nicknames.

108
00:05:33,733 --> 00:05:35,267
What would you like yours to be?

109
00:05:35,268 --> 00:05:36,636
A nickname?

110
00:05:37,203 --> 00:05:38,837
Then…

111
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,172
Please call me Shi-chan.

112
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:42,374
Very nice!

113
00:05:42,375 --> 00:05:43,810
Attention everyone!

114
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:47,479
This is Shi-chan, who will be joining
as the newest staff member!

115
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:48,547
- Hello.
- Shi-chan.

116
00:05:48,548 --> 00:05:50,316
- Shi-chan!
- Nice to meet you.

117
00:05:53,686 --> 00:05:54,620
Nice to meet you.

118
00:05:55,555 --> 00:05:57,155
Whoa, watch out. Don't cut me.

119
00:05:57,156 --> 00:05:59,324
Basically, everyone here just hangs out

120
00:05:59,325 --> 00:06:01,660
and does whatever they feel like doing.

121
00:06:01,661 --> 00:06:03,695
They can do homework,

122
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:04,996
play games,

123
00:06:04,997 --> 00:06:07,800
or even just take a nap
like that kid over there.

124
00:06:08,401 --> 00:06:11,404
There are no specific rules here?

125
00:06:12,004 --> 00:06:16,409
Well, they have to put their belongings
in a locker when they get here.

126
00:06:17,176 --> 00:06:19,678
And they have to throw away trash
in the wastebasket.

127
00:06:19,679 --> 00:06:21,179
Throw trash in the wastebasket.

128
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:22,114
I see.

129
00:06:22,115 --> 00:06:25,917
I know there are various types
of alternative schools,

130
00:06:25,918 --> 00:06:26,819
but what type is this…

131
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:30,123
This is the safe haven type.

132
00:06:31,457 --> 00:06:32,925
Safe haven type.

133
00:06:35,161 --> 00:06:37,663
This is the kitchen and dining room area.

134
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,031
They're making lunch?

135
00:06:40,032 --> 00:06:42,634
Yeah. Hey guys, what's on the menu today?

136
00:06:42,635 --> 00:06:44,870
Curry with fried chicken and salad.

137
00:06:44,871 --> 00:06:46,571
How many layers of the onion do I peel?

138
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:47,572
I'll do it.

139
00:06:47,573 --> 00:06:49,108
All right.

140
00:06:49,675 --> 00:06:50,942
Hello. I'm Ajiki.

141
00:06:50,943 --> 00:06:52,210
Hello.

142
00:06:52,211 --> 00:06:54,313
I'm Shizuku Aomine.

143
00:06:55,481 --> 00:06:56,982
Call me Shi-chan.

144
00:06:56,983 --> 00:06:58,483
I'm Ajicchan. Nice to meet you.

145
00:06:58,484 --> 00:06:59,852
Nice to meet you.

146
00:07:00,553 --> 00:07:03,488
Everyone cooks together?

147
00:07:03,489 --> 00:07:05,323
Once a week.
And participation is optional.

148
00:07:05,324 --> 00:07:07,259
We all decide on the menu together.

149
00:07:07,260 --> 00:07:08,760
We made gratin last week.

150
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:10,228
- Oh.
- I see.

151
00:07:10,229 --> 00:07:11,797
Please make the salad.

152
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:13,131
Just tear up the lettuce.

153
00:07:13,132 --> 00:07:14,466
- Oh, but…
- Thanks.

154
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:15,934
Just tear it?

155
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:17,536
- Let's see…
- Oh!

156
00:07:17,537 --> 00:07:20,305
Shi-chan, can you show the guests
to the atelier?

157
00:07:20,306 --> 00:07:21,908
- Me?
- Yeah, sorry.

158
00:07:22,708 --> 00:07:24,544
I'm Saotome.

159
00:07:27,513 --> 00:07:28,614
Say hello.

160
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:35,488
She's Ayaka.

161
00:07:36,956 --> 00:07:38,690
She had been skipping school

162
00:07:38,691 --> 00:07:41,394
on and off during the first year
of middle school,

163
00:07:41,894 --> 00:07:43,762
but ever since she started
the second year,

164
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:45,598
she's been unable to go to school at all.

165
00:07:46,165 --> 00:07:47,400
I see.

166
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:51,536
Lately, her days and nights
have gotten completely flipped around,

167
00:07:51,537 --> 00:07:52,738
and her lifestyle is irregular,

168
00:07:53,539 --> 00:07:57,443
so I'm hoping to get her back
to a normal routine.

169
00:08:05,318 --> 00:08:08,020
All this artwork was drawn
by the kids here.

170
00:08:09,655 --> 00:08:10,556
Isn't this interesting?

171
00:08:12,725 --> 00:08:15,461
Since she's been refusing
to go to school for so long,

172
00:08:15,962 --> 00:08:18,431
I'm worried that she'll fall behind
on her studies.

173
00:08:22,468 --> 00:08:23,336
That's understandable.

174
00:08:23,903 --> 00:08:27,973
How are the kids here studying…?

175
00:08:27,974 --> 00:08:29,775
They hardly study at all.

176
00:08:30,943 --> 00:08:34,480
They usually play games,
go outside to play, or draw.

177
00:08:35,147 --> 00:08:35,982
I'm sorry.

178
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:40,886
I'm usually playing games
until late at night,

179
00:08:40,887 --> 00:08:42,455
so I'm sleep-deprived every day.

180
00:08:43,890 --> 00:08:45,324
- I see.
- Yup.

181
00:08:46,959 --> 00:08:48,393
If you want to get her to study,

182
00:08:48,394 --> 00:08:50,863
you'll be better off throwing away
the textbooks altogether.

183
00:08:51,664 --> 00:08:52,632
‎What?

184
00:08:55,268 --> 00:08:58,904
I actually used to work
as a middle school teacher.

185
00:08:58,905 --> 00:09:01,339
So I can help out with the schoolwork.

186
00:09:01,340 --> 00:09:02,575
I see.

187
00:09:03,609 --> 00:09:04,443
Good for you.

188
00:09:06,746 --> 00:09:09,849
Did Ayaka say
that she wanted to come here?

189
00:09:11,651 --> 00:09:13,652
I checked the reviews online,

190
00:09:13,653 --> 00:09:15,987
and when I told her about this place,

191
00:09:15,988 --> 00:09:18,558
she said she wanted to check it out.

192
00:09:19,191 --> 00:09:20,359
I see.

193
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:25,730
How long do people stay here
for their school refusal to be cured?

194
00:09:25,731 --> 00:09:27,300
It's not something that can be cured.

195
00:09:29,268 --> 00:09:31,370
Not going to school is also a way of life.

196
00:09:34,941 --> 00:09:37,009
But in that case, what about her future…

197
00:09:37,810 --> 00:09:40,613
What matters more is the present,
not the future.

198
00:09:46,419 --> 00:09:48,688
Do you have any other concerns?

199
00:09:50,323 --> 00:09:51,157
No, thank you.

200
00:09:51,924 --> 00:09:52,892
Okay.

201
00:09:54,627 --> 00:09:57,229
While you're here,
only do things that you think are fun.

202
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:01,167
Want to draw something?

203
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:03,669
Let's see.

204
00:10:04,170 --> 00:10:06,004
This might be good.

205
00:10:06,005 --> 00:10:08,407
- Thank you for the food.
- Let's eat.

206
00:10:09,342 --> 00:10:10,442
Yummy!

207
00:10:10,443 --> 00:10:12,310
It's delicious!

208
00:10:12,311 --> 00:10:13,912
Make sure you chew your food.

209
00:10:13,913 --> 00:10:16,615
Curry is not a drink, got it?

210
00:10:16,616 --> 00:10:18,016
Stop that.

211
00:10:18,017 --> 00:10:19,986
I understand you must be worried.

212
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,355
Yes.

213
00:10:23,656 --> 00:10:28,661
I'm not really sure what's troubling her.

214
00:10:30,129 --> 00:10:32,264
Even when I ask, she won't tell me.

215
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:38,870
Did anything change around the time
she started the second year?

216
00:10:38,871 --> 00:10:40,940
For example, were there any school events?

217
00:10:45,378 --> 00:10:47,513
You can draw whatever you want.

218
00:10:48,514 --> 00:10:49,482
All right.

219
00:10:50,249 --> 00:10:51,784
Okay.

220
00:10:58,457 --> 00:11:00,526
How about we play word chain art?

221
00:11:03,129 --> 00:11:04,363
I'll start.

222
00:11:06,365 --> 00:11:08,067
Let's see.

223
00:11:18,277 --> 00:11:19,111
Your turn.

224
00:11:34,293 --> 00:11:35,227
All right.

225
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:39,832
Let's see what I can do.

226
00:11:43,169 --> 00:11:45,771
Maybe I'll add color to it.

227
00:11:55,981 --> 00:11:59,451
When you use your finger
to blend the color like this…

228
00:11:59,452 --> 00:12:00,953
It looks good, right?

229
00:12:02,688 --> 00:12:07,059
If we're going to use soft pastels…

230
00:12:11,297 --> 00:12:13,165
This drawing paper would be best.

231
00:12:13,966 --> 00:12:14,800
Here.

232
00:12:38,924 --> 00:12:41,427
Is that a sparrow?

233
00:12:50,402 --> 00:12:52,638
That looks good. Draw some more.

234
00:13:11,157 --> 00:13:13,125
That one is all alone.

235
00:13:17,229 --> 00:13:18,297
I guess so.

236
00:13:20,166 --> 00:13:21,066
I see.

237
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:30,976
How does that sparrow feel?

238
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:51,564
This area is empty. Can I draw here?

239
00:13:54,133 --> 00:13:55,301
You drew a sparrow,

240
00:13:55,801 --> 00:13:57,135
so I'll draw the next one.

241
00:13:57,136 --> 00:14:00,505
Let's see, I'll draw…

242
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:01,540
I don't know.

243
00:14:26,565 --> 00:14:28,567
Let's continue this next time.

244
00:14:33,806 --> 00:14:38,610
NOT GOING TO SCHOOL
IS ALSO ONE WAY OF LIFE

245
00:14:38,611 --> 00:14:39,944
- Bye.
- Bye.

246
00:14:39,945 --> 00:14:41,513
- Bye.
- Be careful.

247
00:14:43,015 --> 00:14:45,283
Sorry for causing you so much trouble.

248
00:14:45,284 --> 00:14:46,819
Not at all.

249
00:14:47,820 --> 00:14:49,922
Throwing that playdough
helped you blow off steam, right?

250
00:14:50,589 --> 00:14:51,823
Bye.

251
00:14:51,824 --> 00:14:55,060
It seems like he constantly
throws tantrums at school too.

252
00:14:56,595 --> 00:14:57,429
You can do it.

253
00:14:58,364 --> 00:15:01,567
- I did it!
- Yeah!

254
00:15:05,237 --> 00:15:06,338
Stop it!

255
00:15:08,240 --> 00:15:10,375
Whoa, let's get away from him!

256
00:15:10,376 --> 00:15:12,478
<i>I ask him why he'd do such a thing,</i>

257
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:14,012
but to no avail.

258
00:15:14,013 --> 00:15:15,146
- Bye.
- Bye.

259
00:15:15,147 --> 00:15:15,981
Well,

260
00:15:16,649 --> 00:15:20,052
if you ever feel like really letting loose
and throwing something again,

261
00:15:20,719 --> 00:15:22,553
we've got Ms. Shizuku here.

262
00:15:22,554 --> 00:15:24,722
Hold on, I'm not a shooting target.

263
00:15:24,723 --> 00:15:27,159
- I'm really sorry.
- It's all right.

264
00:15:27,726 --> 00:15:28,960
We'll be going now.

265
00:15:28,961 --> 00:15:29,795
Bye.

266
00:15:34,700 --> 00:15:36,669
Ayaka. See you again.

267
00:15:44,743 --> 00:15:45,944
I'm back.

268
00:15:45,945 --> 00:15:48,180
Welcome home. How was it?

269
00:15:50,516 --> 00:15:51,350
I drew.

270
00:15:52,885 --> 00:15:53,719
That's good.

271
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:56,188
I'm glad you had fun.

272
00:16:03,195 --> 00:16:05,264
About school tomorrow…

273
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:10,502
Never mind.

274
00:16:15,174 --> 00:16:16,742
Good work, everyone.

275
00:16:17,943 --> 00:16:19,410
- Hello, Professor.
- Hello.

276
00:16:19,411 --> 00:16:21,379
I started working here today.

277
00:16:21,380 --> 00:16:22,680
This is Shi-chan.

278
00:16:22,681 --> 00:16:23,848
- I'm Shi-chan.
- Shi-chan?

279
00:16:23,849 --> 00:16:25,117
- Nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

280
00:16:26,318 --> 00:16:27,519
This is for everyone.

281
00:16:28,587 --> 00:16:29,887
You were on a trip?

282
00:16:29,888 --> 00:16:32,190
It was an academic conference
for art therapy.

283
00:16:32,191 --> 00:16:33,092
Oh, right.

284
00:16:34,226 --> 00:16:35,361
What's art therapy?

285
00:16:36,095 --> 00:16:37,962
I'm not entirely sure myself,

286
00:16:37,963 --> 00:16:40,932
but I guess it's something like
expressing your feelings

287
00:16:40,933 --> 00:16:43,868
and finding healing through art.

288
00:16:43,869 --> 00:16:45,937
Shi-chan, how was your first day?

289
00:16:45,938 --> 00:16:48,940
Well, it was one surprise after another.

290
00:16:48,941 --> 00:16:51,275
I realized everyone
is free to do whatever they want.

291
00:16:51,276 --> 00:16:53,344
Whether that's drawing or playing games.

292
00:16:53,345 --> 00:16:54,245
That's right.

293
00:16:54,246 --> 00:16:57,148
Yeah, our policy is to leave everything
up to the kids.

294
00:16:57,149 --> 00:16:59,917
They're free to play video games,
and free to do sports.

295
00:16:59,918 --> 00:17:01,252
- Right?
- Yeah.

296
00:17:01,253 --> 00:17:04,655
But Ayaka's mother, who visited today,

297
00:17:04,656 --> 00:17:06,959
was worried about her daughter's studies.

298
00:17:07,659 --> 00:17:08,860
Mr. Tatsuki told her

299
00:17:08,861 --> 00:17:11,764
that if she wants her to study,
she should throw away her textbooks.

300
00:17:13,132 --> 00:17:16,067
It's true that for some kids,
seeing textbooks lined up on the shelf

301
00:17:16,068 --> 00:17:17,603
can become a source of pressure.

302
00:17:19,204 --> 00:17:22,106
So, one approach is to remove the books
out of sight once

303
00:17:22,107 --> 00:17:24,709
and wait until they regain
the desire to study again.

304
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:26,411
I see.

305
00:17:26,412 --> 00:17:27,846
That's why they need to be tossed.

306
00:17:28,447 --> 00:17:29,681
They shouldn't be tossed away.

307
00:17:30,315 --> 00:17:32,351
Ayaka was drawing today.

308
00:17:33,118 --> 00:17:35,686
Oh, she drew, huh?
I want to take a look at it.

309
00:17:35,687 --> 00:17:36,855
- This way.
- Let me see it.

310
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:39,992
First we played word chain art,

311
00:17:40,859 --> 00:17:41,927
then she drew this.

312
00:17:45,364 --> 00:17:46,932
Did she mention anything about school?

313
00:17:48,067 --> 00:17:49,301
No, nothing.

314
00:17:49,868 --> 00:17:51,036
I see.

315
00:17:52,004 --> 00:17:52,871
Um…

316
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:58,143
I heard from Ayaka's mother today…

317
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:02,881
Did anything change around the time
she started the second year?

318
00:18:05,884 --> 00:18:08,854
There was a field trip.

319
00:18:10,055 --> 00:18:11,590
Field trip, huh.

320
00:18:12,691 --> 00:18:15,594
Something might've happened
between her and her friends.

321
00:18:17,062 --> 00:18:19,263
Can I look into this a little?

322
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:20,698
No need to do that.

323
00:18:20,699 --> 00:18:22,267
It's better to resolve this quickly.

324
00:18:23,035 --> 00:18:25,470
I know a few teachers
at Kita Middle School.

325
00:18:25,471 --> 00:18:28,339
I think she'll tell us the details
when she's ready to.

326
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:30,208
Now, now.

327
00:18:30,209 --> 00:18:31,510
Just ask around casually.

328
00:18:32,177 --> 00:18:33,178
Okay.

329
00:18:39,351 --> 00:18:42,121
By the way, how's that kid
who throws tantrums?

330
00:18:42,654 --> 00:18:43,555
Yuuki?

331
00:18:44,456 --> 00:18:45,424
How's he doing?

332
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:51,662
I allowed him
to really let loose today, but…

333
00:18:51,663 --> 00:18:52,964
- Get away!
- Ouch!

334
00:18:52,965 --> 00:18:53,866
Strike 'em down!

335
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:57,603
I honestly don't know if that was
the right thing to do.

336
00:19:00,506 --> 00:19:02,607
Then the next step

337
00:19:02,608 --> 00:19:05,377
is to figure out how to help him
control those emotions.

338
00:19:06,211 --> 00:19:07,045
Control?

339
00:19:10,048 --> 00:19:11,983
Well, I'm off now.

340
00:19:11,984 --> 00:19:13,152
Bye.

341
00:19:20,292 --> 00:19:21,526
<i>Don't come in here!</i>

342
00:19:21,527 --> 00:19:22,794
Go away!

343
00:19:25,297 --> 00:19:26,398
Sora! Open up!

344
00:19:31,970 --> 00:19:34,706
MUSASHINO KITA MIDDLE SCHOOL

345
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:49,654
Ms. Aomine,

346
00:19:49,655 --> 00:19:50,955
long time no see.

347
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:52,523
Sorry to bother you like this.

348
00:19:52,524 --> 00:19:53,591
Not at all.

349
00:19:53,592 --> 00:19:57,328
We want to address the issue
of school refusal as soon as possible,

350
00:19:57,329 --> 00:20:00,432
- so this is actually a big help.
- Thank you.

351
00:20:00,999 --> 00:20:03,467
He was in the same group as her
during the field trip,

352
00:20:03,468 --> 00:20:05,771
and he seems to know a little
about the situation.

353
00:20:06,738 --> 00:20:08,273
Sorry to bother you during lunch.

354
00:20:08,774 --> 00:20:09,808
Not at all.

355
00:20:10,809 --> 00:20:14,145
Do you have any idea why Ayaka

356
00:20:14,146 --> 00:20:16,982
stopped coming to school?

357
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:19,451
It's probably

358
00:20:21,119 --> 00:20:22,321
my fault.

359
00:20:32,297 --> 00:20:34,433
Hey, it's almost time to meet up
with everyone.

360
00:20:35,867 --> 00:20:36,768
You're not done yet?

361
00:20:40,872 --> 00:20:41,840
We'll be going now.

362
00:20:46,044 --> 00:20:47,045
Let's go.

363
00:20:47,879 --> 00:20:49,914
<i>I didn't say anything more</i>

364
00:20:49,915 --> 00:20:51,917
<i>and we left her there.</i>

365
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,457
Thanks for telling me.

366
00:21:04,596 --> 00:21:05,564
That's so cool.

367
00:21:11,503 --> 00:21:12,471
- Damn it!
- Yuuki!

368
00:21:31,823 --> 00:21:32,858
Yuuki.

369
00:21:35,927 --> 00:21:38,363
This car is just like you.

370
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:42,401
- What?
- Look.

371
00:21:43,702 --> 00:21:46,338
It has the ability to go super-fast!

372
00:21:49,207 --> 00:21:50,809
When it's angry,
it has strong attack power.

373
00:21:54,479 --> 00:21:55,547
That's like me?

374
00:22:01,086 --> 00:22:02,487
Try driving it yourself.

375
00:22:09,528 --> 00:22:11,863
Try driving it slowly.

376
00:22:14,299 --> 00:22:15,233
Vroom, vroom.

377
00:22:15,801 --> 00:22:17,568
- Vroom, vroom.
- Good.

378
00:22:17,569 --> 00:22:18,904
Make it go even slower.

379
00:22:19,638 --> 00:22:20,772
I want it to go faster.

380
00:22:22,007 --> 00:22:24,643
Then try gradually increasing the speed.

381
00:22:33,151 --> 00:22:34,820
- Vroom, vroom!
- That's good!

382
00:22:36,221 --> 00:22:38,623
Little by little. Good job.

383
00:22:40,659 --> 00:22:42,259
Yuuki. Stop.

384
00:22:42,260 --> 00:22:43,462
Stop!

385
00:22:45,597 --> 00:22:47,966
Good job, Yuuki. Excellent driver.

386
00:22:49,267 --> 00:22:50,569
Hey.

387
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:55,774
If you ever reach a point
when you feel overwhelmed,

388
00:22:56,942 --> 00:22:57,976
think about this car.

389
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:07,753
Mr. Tatsuki.

390
00:23:10,789 --> 00:23:13,424
So according to that group leader,
the source of the issue

391
00:23:13,425 --> 00:23:16,293
might be the fact that Ayaka
ended up getting left behind

392
00:23:16,294 --> 00:23:19,231
because she was so absorbed
with her drawing.

393
00:23:20,232 --> 00:23:21,066
And then?

394
00:23:22,501 --> 00:23:25,470
It seems he's going to apologize
to Ayaka in person today.

395
00:23:36,515 --> 00:23:39,784
We're very sorry.

396
00:23:39,785 --> 00:23:40,619
Not at all.

397
00:23:41,186 --> 00:23:43,455
Thank you for coming all the way here.

398
00:23:44,689 --> 00:23:45,724
See you at school.

399
00:23:47,759 --> 00:23:49,428
Thank you for your time today.

400
00:23:49,928 --> 00:23:51,163
Thank you.

401
00:23:55,834 --> 00:23:57,102
I see.

402
00:23:58,837 --> 00:24:00,005
So that's what happened?

403
00:24:03,975 --> 00:24:07,112
But it's nice that he came to apologize.

404
00:24:07,712 --> 00:24:08,680
Can you go to school?

405
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:11,183
Yeah.

406
00:24:11,917 --> 00:24:12,751
Okay.

407
00:24:13,585 --> 00:24:16,421
I'm glad! I'm really glad.

408
00:24:21,293 --> 00:24:23,694
Good morning.

409
00:24:23,695 --> 00:24:24,728
That's nice.

410
00:24:24,729 --> 00:24:26,363
- It's crazy, right?
- Yeah.

411
00:24:26,364 --> 00:24:28,533
So then what happened?

412
00:24:36,274 --> 00:24:37,576
Playing any games lately?

413
00:24:49,254 --> 00:24:51,188
First period we have music.

414
00:24:51,189 --> 00:24:52,590
- Oh, no.
- Oh, crap.

415
00:24:52,591 --> 00:24:53,924
I totally forgot.

416
00:24:53,925 --> 00:24:55,159
Let's hurry.

417
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,060
Oh no.

418
00:24:56,061 --> 00:24:57,295
This is bad.

419
00:25:11,810 --> 00:25:12,710
<i>Ayaka</i>

420
00:25:12,711 --> 00:25:14,513
hasn't come back after that one time.

421
00:25:15,013 --> 00:25:16,882
It seems like she went to school today.

422
00:25:18,283 --> 00:25:20,084
I hope things are going well.

423
00:25:20,085 --> 00:25:21,186
Yeah.

424
00:25:22,721 --> 00:25:25,489
I've experienced school refusal myself,
but the longer it drags on,

425
00:25:25,490 --> 00:25:27,292
the harder it gets to go back.

426
00:25:29,594 --> 00:25:30,662
Is that right?

427
00:25:31,897 --> 00:25:34,198
That's why I can kind of understand

428
00:25:34,199 --> 00:25:36,201
Ayaka's feelings.

429
00:25:43,708 --> 00:25:44,743
Hello, it's Yukanai.

430
00:25:45,644 --> 00:25:47,579
Is Ayaka there?

431
00:25:48,446 --> 00:25:50,315
No, she's not here.

432
00:25:51,449 --> 00:25:53,751
I just got a call from her school.

433
00:25:53,752 --> 00:25:55,820
It seems she left school
without telling anyone.

434
00:25:58,223 --> 00:25:59,424
I'll search for her too.

435
00:26:30,055 --> 00:26:32,824
Shall we continue drawing
where we left off?

436
00:26:34,225 --> 00:26:35,126
‎What?

437
00:26:41,466 --> 00:26:42,367
Here.

438
00:26:46,538 --> 00:26:47,772
With pastels,

439
00:26:48,406 --> 00:26:50,541
you can erase them if you want,

440
00:26:50,542 --> 00:26:51,876
or you can layer them.

441
00:26:52,510 --> 00:26:53,712
You're free to do whatever.

442
00:26:57,415 --> 00:27:00,485
I wonder why she left school early.

443
00:27:02,053 --> 00:27:02,887
Yeah, I wonder.

444
00:27:20,905 --> 00:27:23,108
Do you like to draw?

445
00:27:26,678 --> 00:27:29,247
When I was in college,
I spent all my time drawing.

446
00:27:30,081 --> 00:27:32,083
Can you draw too, Teacher?

447
00:27:33,051 --> 00:27:34,052
Call me Tatsuki.

448
00:27:34,886 --> 00:27:36,321
Tatsuki, draw with me.

449
00:28:09,154 --> 00:28:09,988
What's that?

450
00:28:11,356 --> 00:28:12,190
It's a birdcage.

451
00:28:16,127 --> 00:28:19,364
Those birds are in the birdcage?

452
00:28:21,232 --> 00:28:22,367
Then

453
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:24,669
is that other bird

454
00:28:25,303 --> 00:28:27,372
planning to fly off somewhere?

455
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:38,349
I don't know.

456
00:28:41,486 --> 00:28:42,353
I see.

457
00:28:58,136 --> 00:29:00,672
Ayaka's mother contacted us.

458
00:29:01,339 --> 00:29:03,575
She said Ayaka just got back home.

459
00:29:07,712 --> 00:29:10,115
Did you understand anything
from her drawings?

460
00:29:12,884 --> 00:29:13,985
Nope.

461
00:29:15,053 --> 00:29:17,288
I don't know what Ayaka is going through.

462
00:29:18,823 --> 00:29:20,692
Is it still difficult

463
00:29:21,259 --> 00:29:22,527
even with art therapy?

464
00:29:25,697 --> 00:29:27,932
It doesn't always give us direct answers.

465
00:29:31,469 --> 00:29:35,038
Could it be
that this birdcage and the sparrows

466
00:29:35,039 --> 00:29:37,542
represent her school and friends?

467
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:40,111
From Ayaka's perspective

468
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:44,282
maybe there's this insurmountable wall
keeping her from going to school.

469
00:29:45,250 --> 00:29:46,551
She doesn't need to go.

470
00:29:49,721 --> 00:29:52,056
You don't have to force yourself
to go to school.

471
00:29:52,557 --> 00:29:53,558
Those who want to should go.

472
00:29:54,159 --> 00:29:56,194
That's not how it works.

473
00:29:58,563 --> 00:30:01,799
Ms. Shizuku, you sound just like
a schoolteacher.

474
00:30:01,800 --> 00:30:04,535
Couldn't you be a little more flexible
in your thinking?

475
00:30:04,536 --> 00:30:05,436
No.

476
00:30:06,237 --> 00:30:08,539
Just imagine how worried parents get

477
00:30:08,540 --> 00:30:10,108
when their child won't go to school.

478
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:15,446
I'm sure deep down Ayaka knows this too.

479
00:30:16,347 --> 00:30:18,216
She wants to go but she can't.

480
00:30:19,484 --> 00:30:21,119
But if she continues to stay home,

481
00:30:21,986 --> 00:30:23,955
she knows she'll never
be able to go at all.

482
00:30:25,056 --> 00:30:25,890
That's why

483
00:30:26,691 --> 00:30:28,525
she makes the effort to go.

484
00:30:28,526 --> 00:30:30,028
No one needs to force themselves to go.

485
00:30:30,595 --> 00:30:31,796
What?

486
00:30:33,431 --> 00:30:36,000
I'm going to step out.
Take care of things here.

487
00:30:44,642 --> 00:30:45,476
He's so annoying!

488
00:30:46,878 --> 00:30:49,880
Shi-chan, eat slowly.

489
00:30:49,881 --> 00:30:51,448
What's wrong with that guy?

490
00:30:51,449 --> 00:30:53,952
He's got a super naive mindset,
but is he all right?

491
00:30:55,119 --> 00:30:57,021
I totally understand. It's worrisome, huh?

492
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:00,858
I understand that this place

493
00:31:00,859 --> 00:31:03,727
is necessary
for children who have been hurt.

494
00:31:03,728 --> 00:31:05,596
But it's only natural for parents

495
00:31:05,597 --> 00:31:07,564
to be worried about their children's

496
00:31:07,565 --> 00:31:08,932
studies and their future.

497
00:31:08,933 --> 00:31:10,567
You're right.

498
00:31:10,568 --> 00:31:14,104
And yet he says kids should be free
and not be forced to go to school.

499
00:31:14,105 --> 00:31:16,240
Isn't that just completely irresponsible?

500
00:31:16,241 --> 00:31:19,077
I understand,
but that's too much hot sauce.

501
00:31:21,079 --> 00:31:22,112
Sorry.

502
00:31:22,113 --> 00:31:25,515
Personally, I think it's great to have
different perspectives.

503
00:31:25,516 --> 00:31:27,184
Given your background as a teacher,

504
00:31:27,185 --> 00:31:29,319
you're able to empathize
with parents' feelings.

505
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:31,456
That's necessary here too.

506
00:31:32,090 --> 00:31:33,725
Thank you.

507
00:31:34,325 --> 00:31:37,694
Well, it seems like he has his own way
of dealing with things.

508
00:31:37,695 --> 00:31:38,830
Or so I think.

509
00:31:41,666 --> 00:31:43,001
He's so annoying!

510
00:31:48,573 --> 00:31:50,141
I thought the problem was solved.

511
00:31:50,708 --> 00:31:52,210
The other kid apologized, right?

512
00:31:53,244 --> 00:31:55,379
But she left school early, so I think

513
00:31:55,380 --> 00:31:56,880
there's something else going on.

514
00:31:56,881 --> 00:31:58,116
Like what?

515
00:31:59,050 --> 00:32:00,852
What did Ayaka say?

516
00:32:01,886 --> 00:32:05,290
I've asked her, but she won't tell me.

517
00:32:06,057 --> 00:32:07,758
But even so,

518
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:09,427
we can't just leave this problem alone.

519
00:32:10,128 --> 00:32:12,163
And what if she falls behind
in her studies?

520
00:32:13,231 --> 00:32:15,266
She's the one who'll struggle
in the future.

521
00:32:16,601 --> 00:32:19,836
It's best to solve this
as soon as possible.

522
00:32:19,837 --> 00:32:20,672
Yeah.

523
00:32:30,381 --> 00:32:31,449
I'll be off.

524
00:32:32,483 --> 00:32:33,318
Bye.

525
00:33:11,689 --> 00:33:13,156
- Wait up.
- Okay.

526
00:33:13,157 --> 00:33:15,459
- You can't run into the street.
- I can do a new trick.

527
00:33:15,460 --> 00:33:17,561
- Just watch.
- Go play over there.

528
00:33:17,562 --> 00:33:18,463
Okay.

529
00:33:20,298 --> 00:33:21,965
Oh.

530
00:33:21,966 --> 00:33:22,900
Ayaka.

531
00:33:27,939 --> 00:33:29,106
Ta-da!

532
00:33:29,107 --> 00:33:32,210
A 242-color set of soft pastels!

533
00:33:32,744 --> 00:33:35,012
There were so many colors
I had run out of.

534
00:33:35,013 --> 00:33:36,114
So I decided to splurge.

535
00:33:37,115 --> 00:33:38,248
I see.

536
00:33:38,249 --> 00:33:39,182
Look at this.

537
00:33:39,183 --> 00:33:42,186
The gradation from green to blue
is so cool, isn't it?

538
00:33:43,821 --> 00:33:44,856
Yeah, it's cool.

539
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:48,192
Here.

540
00:33:49,327 --> 00:33:50,161
Go ahead.

541
00:33:50,895 --> 00:33:51,796
Feel free to use it.

542
00:34:35,440 --> 00:34:37,041
It's raining?

543
00:34:45,850 --> 00:34:47,452
That sparrow will get wet.

544
00:34:48,319 --> 00:34:49,353
What's it going to do?

545
00:35:08,239 --> 00:35:09,507
Tatsuki.

546
00:35:18,916 --> 00:35:20,084
Tatsuki.

547
00:35:26,724 --> 00:35:27,859
I don't

548
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:29,994
want to go to school.

549
00:35:35,600 --> 00:35:36,534
I see.

550
00:35:40,605 --> 00:35:42,473
You were able to express your feelings.

551
00:35:52,283 --> 00:35:53,251
If

552
00:35:54,318 --> 00:35:56,254
you have something you want to say,

553
00:35:57,955 --> 00:35:59,790
don't keep it bottled up inside.

554
00:36:00,691 --> 00:36:02,660
You can talk about anything you like here.

555
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:07,098
Okay,

556
00:36:09,767 --> 00:36:11,269
you don't want to go to school, huh.

557
00:36:14,739 --> 00:36:17,942
I've always been scared
of being in the classroom.

558
00:36:22,513 --> 00:36:23,581
But

559
00:36:26,918 --> 00:36:28,452
I couldn't tell anyone about it.

560
00:36:30,788 --> 00:36:32,056
I see.

561
00:36:33,291 --> 00:36:34,725
That's understandable.

562
00:36:37,862 --> 00:36:38,863
And…

563
00:36:42,500 --> 00:36:44,302
I can't tell Mom about this.

564
00:36:50,107 --> 00:36:50,942
Okay.

565
00:36:53,077 --> 00:36:55,145
I see.

566
00:36:55,146 --> 00:36:57,380
I suppose the stifling pressure

567
00:36:57,381 --> 00:37:00,718
of school life just gradually built up
over time.

568
00:37:02,853 --> 00:37:05,923
But it's amazing that she was able
to voice that herself.

569
00:37:06,424 --> 00:37:09,427
But she said she can't bring herself
to tell her mom yet.

570
00:37:11,162 --> 00:37:13,863
It must be tough
when you can't reach out for help

571
00:37:13,864 --> 00:37:15,299
- to the person closest to you.
- Yes.

572
00:37:19,470 --> 00:37:21,372
I don't know how to help her.

573
00:37:23,641 --> 00:37:27,278
To truly understand Ayaka's feelings,

574
00:37:27,812 --> 00:37:29,647
you might need to take a deeper look

575
00:37:30,214 --> 00:37:32,616
at whatever she focuses on

576
00:37:32,617 --> 00:37:34,685
and pours her energy into.

577
00:37:42,493 --> 00:37:44,527
I thought you hated schools.

578
00:37:44,528 --> 00:37:46,162
I never said that.

579
00:37:46,163 --> 00:37:48,698
You were totally against it.

580
00:37:48,699 --> 00:37:51,801
I only got permission on the condition
that we stay in the hallway,

581
00:37:51,802 --> 00:37:53,637
so please don't go into the classroom…

582
00:37:53,638 --> 00:37:55,273
Hey, weren't you listening?

583
00:37:56,274 --> 00:37:59,075
I want to look at the artwork
she drew at the zoo.

584
00:37:59,076 --> 00:38:00,511
Oh, come on.

585
00:38:03,314 --> 00:38:04,315
Hey.

586
00:38:05,082 --> 00:38:08,652
MEMORIES FROM THE FIELD TRIP

587
00:38:08,653 --> 00:38:09,887
There it is.

588
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:15,293
AYAKA SAOTOME
CLASS 2-2

589
00:38:28,506 --> 00:38:29,340
Ms. Shizuku.

590
00:38:29,907 --> 00:38:30,741
Yes?

591
00:38:32,243 --> 00:38:33,177
Let's take this drawing.

592
00:38:33,944 --> 00:38:35,812
No, you can't do that!

593
00:38:35,813 --> 00:38:36,747
- What?
- You can't!

594
00:38:38,749 --> 00:38:39,583
This is

595
00:38:40,351 --> 00:38:42,186
what Ayaka drew when she was here.

596
00:38:43,988 --> 00:38:47,358
It seems very lonely.

597
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:50,828
You're referring to this bird?

598
00:38:52,096 --> 00:38:53,898
It looks lonely

599
00:38:54,999 --> 00:38:56,567
being away from its friends.

600
00:38:57,435 --> 00:38:59,770
I thought so too at first.

601
00:39:02,373 --> 00:39:03,541
I thought this was the school,

602
00:39:04,508 --> 00:39:07,010
and while everyone inside is having fun,

603
00:39:07,011 --> 00:39:09,947
she couldn't break down the thick wall
to join everyone.

604
00:39:10,948 --> 00:39:11,915
Yes.

605
00:39:11,916 --> 00:39:12,783
But

606
00:39:13,551 --> 00:39:15,586
I don't think these are her friends,

607
00:39:17,555 --> 00:39:18,956
but her family instead.

608
00:39:22,093 --> 00:39:23,361
What do you mean?

609
00:39:24,762 --> 00:39:27,397
The birdcage isn't a wall
standing in her way,

610
00:39:27,398 --> 00:39:30,768
but rather a barrier
that's protecting her.

611
00:39:32,670 --> 00:39:35,673
Therefore, I don't think this represents
the school,

612
00:39:36,741 --> 00:39:38,676
but her home instead.

613
00:39:40,578 --> 00:39:42,747
Are you saying
that she wants to stay home?

614
00:39:44,348 --> 00:39:47,084
Is there anything that comes to mind?

615
00:39:50,354 --> 00:39:51,255
Well,

616
00:39:52,089 --> 00:39:56,127
Ayaka has always said
that she wants to go to school.

617
00:39:57,128 --> 00:39:58,295
But she told me

618
00:39:59,463 --> 00:40:01,332
that she doesn't want to go to school.

619
00:40:02,166 --> 00:40:03,066
What?

620
00:40:03,067 --> 00:40:05,269
She said she can't bring herself
to tell you about it.

621
00:40:08,706 --> 00:40:09,807
But why?

622
00:40:11,242 --> 00:40:13,477
I didn't understand either, but…

623
00:40:23,621 --> 00:40:25,156
Please take a look at this.

624
00:40:26,424 --> 00:40:30,728
This is what Ayaka drew at the zoo.

625
00:40:31,328 --> 00:40:32,830
When I look at this,

626
00:40:34,031 --> 00:40:35,232
I get the sense

627
00:40:36,267 --> 00:40:38,302
that this parent and child
share a deep bond

628
00:40:39,136 --> 00:40:43,474
and place a great deal of trust
in one another.

629
00:40:46,544 --> 00:40:47,912
That's how it seems

630
00:40:48,979 --> 00:40:51,182
to me too.

631
00:40:55,085 --> 00:40:56,554
I think Ayaka

632
00:40:57,988 --> 00:41:00,191
couldn't bring herself
to express her true feelings

633
00:41:01,258 --> 00:41:03,928
because her mother is so important to her.

634
00:41:27,785 --> 00:41:28,819
Ayaka.

635
00:41:32,189 --> 00:41:33,157
This

636
00:41:34,024 --> 00:41:35,292
is a beautiful drawing.

637
00:41:44,034 --> 00:41:45,636
The truth is,

638
00:41:46,871 --> 00:41:49,340
I never wanted to go to school.

639
00:42:05,222 --> 00:42:08,926
I'm sorry I never told you the truth.

640
00:42:16,901 --> 00:42:17,902
It's all right.

641
00:42:20,137 --> 00:42:21,405
I was always

642
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:25,476
a little too relieved whenever

643
00:42:26,176 --> 00:42:27,778
you went to school, huh?

644
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:33,684
That's why you couldn't
tell me the truth, right?

645
00:42:37,354 --> 00:42:38,522
I'm sorry.

646
00:43:06,750 --> 00:43:09,419
Time to counterattack!

647
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:10,554
Stop!

648
00:43:12,089 --> 00:43:13,824
Hooray!

649
00:43:22,566 --> 00:43:24,335
<i>When you feel overwhelmed,</i>

650
00:43:25,736 --> 00:43:27,304
think about this car.

651
00:43:40,751 --> 00:43:41,651
Time to escape!

652
00:43:41,652 --> 00:43:43,887
- No way.
- Hold on.

653
00:43:48,826 --> 00:43:50,494
You're going to Yukanai today, right?

654
00:43:51,395 --> 00:43:52,363
Here's your lunch.

655
00:43:52,863 --> 00:43:55,499
I put in your favorite Hamburg steak
to cheer you up!

656
00:43:59,169 --> 00:44:00,270
Thank you.

657
00:44:00,971 --> 00:44:03,439
But right now, my favorite food
is <i>kinpira gobo</i>.

658
00:44:03,440 --> 00:44:04,707
It is?

659
00:44:04,708 --> 00:44:06,076
Since when?

660
00:44:06,577 --> 00:44:09,246
Children grow up before you know it.

661
00:44:09,747 --> 00:44:11,515
Oh, is that right?

662
00:44:12,282 --> 00:44:14,618
Then I'll add that to your lunch
next time.

663
00:44:16,887 --> 00:44:17,988
Thank you.

664
00:44:18,689 --> 00:44:19,523
I'll be off.

665
00:44:20,391 --> 00:44:21,225
Have fun.

666
00:44:55,526 --> 00:44:56,459
Hello?

667
00:44:56,460 --> 00:44:58,796
Tatsuki. Sora… Sora…

668
00:44:59,997 --> 00:45:01,164
What happened to Sora?

669
00:45:01,165 --> 00:45:02,900
He jumped.

670
00:45:04,234 --> 00:45:05,069
What?

671
00:45:06,970 --> 00:45:08,905
PREVIEW OF THE NEXT EPISODE

672
00:45:08,906 --> 00:45:10,973
‎THIS DRAMA IS FICTION

673
00:45:10,974 --> 00:45:11,942
Subtitle translation by: Lili Morita
